        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-04-13 15:19:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThose zip files exported by JMeter notoriously have license issues in them. Just checking to see that those have been cleaned out? I thought that we were simply dumping PDFs of the results, but I could be mistaken since these are modifications.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "98e3ccee7bf1cc26301438b52087a6dfb63e94c3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 811,
          "name": "Jim Hahn",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-04-13 15:25:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Those zip files exported by JMeter notoriously have license issues in them. Just checking to see that those have been cleaned out? I thought that we were simply dumping PDFs of the results, but I could be mistaken since these are modifications.\n\nThat's what I remember, too - the result zip should typically be replaced with PDF or PNG files, as the embedded html and/or css files typically have copyrights.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "ca9d47afe7b1a69b1b37f2dd20fb5fc8ce8e292e",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 477,
          "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
          "username": "jhh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-04-13 16:09:00.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI have doubts if there is a lot of value including the zip files as the results will vary somewhat from configuration to configuration, and the size of the cloned repos.   We don't include them in some policy projects.   They could be kept in the wiki as an alternative.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
